Hi everyone,
Krithik from team 2720. We created around 15 auto paths this year for the 2024 season. When we tested doing a 4 note auto from the center spot on the subwoofer, our auto worked somewhat well, however when we did the same for the Amp side of the subwoofer, our pivot arm didn’t run and our whole robot kind of had a spasm and froze.

I have attached videos of both to this post. (Sorry ChiefDelphi is not allowing me to upload videos so I put them in a zip file)
Archive 2.zip (28.6 MB)

We detect the angle to shoot at the speaker based on April tags, but that shouldn’t be a problem since from both positions that our bot starts at we are able to detect the April tag, and we can see it throughout our autos.

Here are photos of the two paths:
Amp side:

Screenshot 2024-03-03 at 5.20.29 PM2388×1146 274 KB

Center side of subwoofer:

Screenshot 2024-03-03 at 5.21.55 PM2450×1362 292 KB
